---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import Section from "../../components/Section.astro";
import Card from "../../components/Card.astro";

const title = "Meta Analysis for One Piece Card Game";
const description = "Weekly One Piece Card Game meta analysis covering top leaders, matchup trends, and format shifts.";
---

<MainLayout title={title} description={description}>
	<section class="hero">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="hero-badge">Meta Analysis</span>
			<h1>Meta Analysis for One Piece Card Game</h1>
			<p>
				Winning consistently starts with understanding the field. Our meta analysis breaks down what is
				performing well, which leaders are rising, and why certain lists convert better than others. We focus
				on data-driven patterns from tournaments and community events, then translate those patterns into
				practical decisions you can bring to your next round.
			</p>
			<p>
				Expect weekly snapshots of top leaders, the interaction packages they lean on, and the matchup
				pressure points that keep them in check. We also highlight tech cards that swing specific pairings
				and explain when they are worth the slot. If you need a leader-specific plan, jump to
				<a href="/deck-guides">Deck Guides</a>. For a focused look at head-to-head play, use
				<a href="/matchups">Matchups</a>. Beginners can start with <a href="/beginner-guides">Beginner Guides</a>
				to build a strong foundation before diving into advanced teching.
			</p>
			<p>
				These updates are built for fast scanning on mobile while keeping the depth needed for tournament
				preparation. You will see format threats, counter options, and the likely next moves as new sets drop
				or the <a href="/banlist">Banlist</a> shifts. Save the pages you rely on so you can react quickly when
				the meta moves.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<Section
		title="Current Meta Snapshots"
		description="Quick reads on what is winning now and how to counter it."
		linkHref="/meta-analysis"
		linkLabel="All meta reports"
	>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Top Cut"
			title="Leaders with Highest Conversion"
			description="Which leaders consistently reach top cut and the core packages they rely on."
			href="/meta-analysis"
		/>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Trend"
			title="Tempo vs. Interaction"
			description="How removal density is shifting deck choices and what it means for your list."
			href="/meta-analysis"
		/>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Tech"
			title="Flexible Answers"
			description="Low-commitment inclusions that improve your worst matchups."
			href="/meta-analysis"
		/>
		<Card
			eyebrow="Forecast"
			title="Next Set Impact"
			description="Early expectations for new leaders and support cards."
			href="/meta-analysis"
		/>
	</Section>
</MainLayout>
